post_text:
Virtual Athenaeum: Sit back and enjoy story time with Ms. Neal from Archway Chandler!
The Kissing Hand is an American children's picture book written by Audrey Penn and illustrated by Ruth E. Harper and Nancy M. Leak. It features a mother raccoon comforting a child raccoon by kissing its paw. It was first published by the Child Welfare League of America in 1993, it has been used to reassure children upset by separation anxiety.

We will continue to post Virtual Athenaeum through the month of June. Be sure to keep your eyes out for our next video!

For more videos and to learn more about After-School Athenaeum, please visit:
www.GreatHeartsAmerica.org/Athenaeum

post_text:
At Archway Trivium East, we value art education as a way to celebrate beauty and cultivate a sense of wonder in our students' hearts and minds. We were delighted to receive this report from a parent:
"While browsing the internet for a new puzzle during this time at home, my son started jumping up and down at the sight of a specific puzzle. This puzzle depicts the famous artist Katsushika Hokusai‚Äôs work, "The Great Wave." I have seen this painting before and knew of its fame, however I did not know the name or anything about it. My 8 year old son on the other hand, told me all about it because he learned about it in his art class."
Thank you to our art teachers for instilling this love of beauty in our students! #archwaytriviumeast #wearetrivium

post_text:
For 24 hours, Arizona will focus on nonprofits and the important role they play in our state and in our communities. All over Arizona people are choosing to give to the nonprofits they believe in. We hope that you believe in and are inspired by the bright and amazing students of Archway Trivium East! In the spirit of this day, please support Archway Trivium East through giving to Community Investment or by giving your Arizona Public School Tax Credit.
Thank you for your consideration as we continue the "Great-Hearted" work of serving all who enter our doors! www.archwaytriviumeast.org/giving
#wearetrivium #archwaytriviumeast

Here's another song from Ms. Sassaman that can be sung in a round. The lyrics are included below. See if you can join in at home! #archwaytriviumeast #wearetrivium

Come Follow by John Hilton (1599-1657)

Come follow, follow, follow,
follow, follow, follow me!

Wither shall I follow, follow, follow,
Wither shall I follow, follow thee?

To the greenwood, to the greenwood,
to the greenwood, greenwood tree.

post_text:
To celebrate our first week of remote learning, we are hosting a Trivium-wide Virtual Spirit Day on Friday, March 27. Students and families are encouraged to wear Spirit Wear or school colors at home on Friday and to share a photo in the comments of a post on our school's Facebook page on that day. On this unique Spirit Day, you could even wear your school uniform! Tag your photos #TriviumSpiritDay #WeAreTrivium.
Also, don't forget to visit our facebook page each morning this week for a video message from the Headmaster.

post_text:
Great Hearts Academies plans to extend spring break at all of our campuses through the week of March 16th. There will be no regular school or after-school activities during this week. We plan to resume classes on March 23, 2020. You can stay informed on our website: https://www.greatheartsamerica.org/coronavirus/
Should we need to extend again, we will tell you as soon as we have made that decision.
We are very sorry for the inconveniences and hardships this may cause, but we sincerely believe it is in the best interest of our community at this time.

post_text:
We are excited for Trivium Prep Varsity Boys Basketball team to continue playing in the state tournament this weekend. On Friday morning they will play in the 2A State Semifinal game!

On Friday, February 28, to celebrate this event, we are having a Trivium-wide Spirit Day! All Archway Trivium East, Archway Trivium West and Trivium Prep students are invited to wear their Spirit Wear or Class t-shirts along with the rest of their uniform (uniform bottoms with belt, shirt tucked in, and uniform shoes). Show your school spirit!

Congratulations to the Trivium Prep Varsity Boys and all of our winter athletes! It's been a great season!

The scholars who presented recitations at the 2019 Athenian Bard Competition performed each poem with confidence and excellence. Of the events we celebrate as a community, no other offers more scholars the opportunity to store so much beauty within their hearts and minds. We are proud of each scholar who participated.
Congratulations goes to Endy Dixon, the 2019 Athenian Bard, for his exceptional recitation of
Casey at the Bat, by Ernest Lawrence Thayer. Endy will represent Archway Trivium East at the Great Hearts Bard Competition on April 10, at 6:00 pm, at Veritas Preparatory Academy in Phoenix. Please join us on that night in support of Endy.

post_text: Congrats to Archway Trivium East student, Srihaas Ghanta, who advanced to the statewide Spelling Bee today!
shared_text:
Great Hearts Academies
February 23, 2019 at 2:49 PM ¬∑

For the first time in Great Hearts history, one of our students has advanced to the statewide Spelling Bee. Srihaas, a 5th grader at Archway Trivium East, not only won the Great Hearts Spelling Bee back in January, but he completed 36 rounds in the regional spelling bee today. His next stop will be the Arizona State Bee in hopes of making it all of the way to the Scripps National Spelling Bee in May. Congratulations!

His next stop will be the Arizona State Bee in hopes of making it all of the way to the Scripps National Spelling Bee in May. Congratulations!

post_text: We were thrilled to have the Arizona Opera perform selections from Mozart's opera, The Magic Flute for our students today. While their pianist performed the orchestral score, the opera singers performed the story of Prince Tamino on his quest to find Princess Pamina with the help of his bird catcher friend Papageno. We were also introduced to the famous Queen of the Night, as well as Sarastro who rules over the Land of the Sun. The singers performed famous arias and scenes, and engaged the audience along the way. It was truly a treat for our students! Performances like these are made possible by your AZ Tax Credit dollars. Thank you to all who have supported our school through your donations!

Current Archway Trivium East parents are invited to join Headmaster Washburn for an informal conversation over coffee on Friday, February 22 at 8:30 AM. This month, our featured topic is "Narration for Detail" presented by 1st grade teacher, Mrs. Moreno.

RSVP online: http://bit.ly/ate-coffee

Coffee conversations are great opportunities to ask questions, share your experiences, and meet other parents. We hope you can join us! Please arrive at least 5 minutes prior to the coffee start time to allow yourself adequate time to park, sign in and receive a visitor pass.
